refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arrayDateTimeZone::getTransitions inttimestamp_begin inttimestamp_end
arraytimezone_transitions_get DateTimeZoneobject inttimestamp_begin inttimestamp_end

&reftitle.parameters;



  &date.datetimezone.description;

   timestamp_begin



     Begin timestamp.




   timestamp_end



     End timestamp.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns numerically indexed array containing associative array with all
 transitions on success or &false; on failure.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     5.3.0

      The optional timestamp_begin and timestamp_end 
      were added.

  &reftitle.examples;



    A timezone_transitions_get example


<?php
$timezone = new DateTimeZone("CET");
print_r(reset($timezone->getTransitions()));
?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


Array
(
    [ts] => -1693706400
    [time] => 1916-04-30T22:00:00+0000
    [offset] => 7200
    [isdst] => 1
    [abbr] => CEST
)
